Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Zest and halve @Lemon{1} (for 4 servings, zest one lemon and halve both). Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tablespoon}, half the @Smoked Paprika{1%teaspoon}, half the @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest of each spice later), @salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Creamy Lemon Slaw ==

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @Sour Cream{2%tablespoon}, juice from half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings), half the @Celery Salt{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), and @Sugar{1.5%teaspoon} (3 tsp for 4). Add @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce} and scallion greens; toss to coat. Season generously with @salt{} and @Pepper{}. Set aside.

== Buns ==

Place @Butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Slice @Demi-Baguette{2%ounce} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through. Spread melted butter onto cut sides of bread. Place, cut sides up, directly on oven rack (or use a baking sheet); toast until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Shrimp ==

While buns toast, rinse @Shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Toss in a second medium bowl with a large drizzle of olive oil, remaining paprika, remaining garlic powder, remaining celery salt, and a big pinch of salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once pan is hot, add shrimp and scallion whites. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are opaque and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and lemon zest to taste.

== Assembly ==

Fill toasted baguettes with shrimp, as much slaw as you like, and @Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired.

Divide shrimp rolls and potato wedges between plates. Slice remaining lemon into wedges and serve on the side.

> TIP: If you have ketchup on hand, serve some on the side for dipping.